---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Cookie Policy | Laravel Mail">
    <main class="py-20 px-6 sm:px-8 lg:px-12 max-w-7xl mx-auto">
        <div class="prose prose-slate max-w-3xl mx-auto">
            <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Cookie Policy</h1>

            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString()}</p>

            <section class="mb-8">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">1. What Are Cookies</h2>
                <p>Cookies are small text files placed on your device when you access a website. They are widely used to help websites function effectively, improve user experience, and provide insights to website owners.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-8">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">2. How We Use Cookies</h2>
                <p>Laravel Mail uses cookies to support the following purposes:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-4">
                    <li><strong>Essential cookies</strong>: Required for the core operation of our platform</li>
                    <li><strong>Analytical/performance cookies</strong>: Help us track usage and improve system performance</li>
                    <li><strong>Functionality cookies</strong>: Remember your preferences and enhance your experience</li>
                    <li><strong>Targeting cookies</strong>: Used by advertising or analytics partners to provide relevant content</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-8">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">3. Types of Cookies We Use</h2>
                <div class="mt-4">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Essential Cookies</h3>
                    <p>These are mandatory for Laravel Mail to function correctly, supporting security, authentication, and accessibility features.</p>

                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 mt-6">Performance Cookies</h3>
                    <p>Used to gather anonymous insights into how our platform is used, so we can continuously improve stability and speed.</p>

                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 mt-6">Functionality Cookies</h3>
                    <p>These remember your login details, preferences, and settings, making your experience smoother when you return.</p>

                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 mt-6">Targeting Cookies</h3>
                    <p>These may be set by trusted third-party partners to deliver relevant marketing or tailor recommendations.</p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-8">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">4. Managing Cookies</h2>
                <p>You can manage or block cookies through your browser settings. Please note, disabling certain cookies may limit some features of Laravel Mail and affect your overall experience. For more information, visit <a href="https://www.aboutcookies.org" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">aboutcookies.org</a>.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-8">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">5. Changes to This Cookie Policy</h2>
                <p>We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time to reflect changes in technology, legislation, or our practices. Updates will be posted on this page with a revised date. Please review this page periodically for the latest information.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-8">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">6. Contact Us</h2>
                <p>If you have any questions about this Cookie Policy or how Laravel Mail uses cookies, please contact us:</p>
                <div class="mt-4">
                    <p>Email: privacy@laravelmail.com</p>
                    <p>Address: 102 A High Street, DA14 6EA, UK</p>
                </div>
            </section>
        </div>
    </main>
</Layout>
